The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has extended the sale of Expression of Interest and Nomination Forms for the Anambra State governorship election. National Organising Secretary, retired Col. Austin Akobundu, made this known in a statement on Wednesday. The forms were sold at N21million – N1million for expression of interest and N20million for nomination form. The closing date for the sale was moved from Wednesday, March 31 to Wednesday, April 7. The date for the submission has also been extended to Saturday, April 10. More than ten aspirants, including three females, have obtained forms ahead of the primary election. They are Sen. Uche Ekwunife (PDP – Anambra), Chidi Onyemelukwe, daughter of ex-Vice President Alex Ekwueme, and Genevieve Ekwochi – Others are Obiora Okonkwo, Chris Azubogu, Winston Ude, Valentine Ozigbo, Godwin Ezeemo, Godwin Maduka, Ifedi Okwenna, Ugochukwu Uba, Tony Nwoye and Walter Okeke.